{"type":"message","id":"39bba4ad","parentId":"98494caf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:56:21.958Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vc2npf3iyn8s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 035513\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The big insight from this session is the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n3. The next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment:\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, specific action I can take right now is to start implementing the TIC experiment. I should:\r\n\r\n1. First, look at the pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a script or document that implements the TIC classifier\r\n3. This is a file edit - I should create a new file or edit an existing one\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC experiment implementation. The most concrete action would be to:\r\n- Create a Python script that analyzes the pulse logs for invariants vs variants\r\n- Or create the initial TIC classifier code\r\n\r\nActually, looking at this more carefully - I need to be concrete. The most actionable thing right now is to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs structure\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nSince the user wants a single concrete action, let me create the core TIC classifier that can analyze the pulse logs for temporal invariance.\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script `src/tic_classifier.py` that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step. I need to implement a classifier that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariants (stable patterns) vs variants (changing content), then validate against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the core TIC classifier implementation that analyzes pulse logs for temporal invariance patterns. This establishes the experimental foundation for the unified Phase 1/Phase 2 compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n================================================\r\nImplements the hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nClassifier finds patterns that persist across pulse boundaries (invariants)\r\nvs patterns that change between pulses (variants).\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    INVARIANT_THRESHOLD = 0.7  # Appears in 70%+ of analyzed pulses\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.pulse_patterns = []  # List of dicts with patterns per pulse\r\n        self.invariant_patterns = set()\r\n        self.variant_patterns = set()\r\n    \r\n    def load_pulses(self, n_recent: int = 20) -> List[Dict]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load the n most recent pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[-n_recent:]\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in pulse_files:\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append({\r\n                'file': f.name,\r\n                'content': content,\r\n                'patterns': self.extract_patterns(content)\r\n            })\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def extract_patterns(self, content: str) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract structural patterns from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n        patterns = {\r\n            'headings': set(re.findall(r'^#+\\s+(.+)$', content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n            'actions': set(re.findall(r'(?:Create|Edit|Implement|Analyze|Build)\\s+\\S+', content)),\r\n            'goals': set(re.findall(r'(?:Phase|Goal|Task)[:\\s]+([^\\n]+)', content, re.I)),\r\n            'files': set(re.findall(r'`([^`]+\\.(?:py|md|ps1|txt))`', content)),\r\n            'concepts': set(re.findall(r'\\b(?:compression|invariant|variant|causal|lambda|decay|temporal)\\b', content, re.I))\r\n        }\r\n        return patterns\r\n    \r\n    def compute_invariants(self, pulses: List[Dict]) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Find patterns that persist across pulses (invariants).\"\"\"\r\n        pattern_frequency = defaultdict(int)\r\n        total_pulses = len(pulses)\r\n        \r\n        # Count frequency of each pattern across all pulses\r\n        for pulse in pulses:\r\n            seen = set()\r\n            for category, patterns in pulse['patterns'].items():\r\n                for p in patterns:\r\n                    key = f\"{category}:{p}\"\r\n                    if key not in seen:\r\n                        pattern_frequency[key] += 1\r\n                        seen.add(key)\r\n        \r\n        # Invariants appear in >= threshold of pulses\r\n        threshold = total_pulses * self.INVARIANT_THRESHOLD\r\n        invariants = {p for p, count in pattern_frequency.items() if count >= threshold}\r\n        return invariants\r\n    \r\n    def compute_variants(self, pulses: List[Dict], invariants: Set[str]) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Find patterns that change between pulses (variants).\"\"\"\r\n        all_patterns = set()\r\n        for pulse in pulses:\r\n            for category, patterns in pulse['patterns'].items():\r\n                for p in patterns:\r\n                    all_patterns.add(f\"{category}:{p}\")\r\n        return all\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:55:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338981956}}
